==評論==
作為被評為全球最獨裁的國家，北韓舉行全國性選舉還是引起了海外傳媒的關注，包括英國的[[BBC|BBC]]、《[[衛報|衛報]]》和美國的《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》、《[[經濟學人|經濟學人]]》等也有報導此事<ref name="bbc">[http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-26502900 "North Koreans vote in rubber-stamp elections"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-26502900 |date=20140316192037 }} BBC News 2014 3 9</ref><ref name="economist">[http://www.economist.com/blogs/economist-explains/2014/03/economist-explains-2?fsrc=scn/fb/wl/bl/ee/hownorthkoreaselectionswork "How North Korea's elections work "] {{Wayback|url=http://www.economist.com/blogs/economist-explains/2014/03/economist-explains-2?fsrc=scn%2Ffb%2Fwl%2Fbl%2Fee%2Fhownorthkoreaselectionswork |date=20180106064535 }} The Economist 2014 3 5</ref><ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/10/world/asia/north-korea.html?_r=0 "North Korea Uses Election To Reshape Parliament"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/10/world/asia/north-korea.html?_r=0 |date=20140313183923 }} New York Times 2014 3 9</ref><ref name="guardian">[http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/10/north-koreas-kim-jong-un-elected-assembly-vote-against "North Korea's Kim Jong-un elected to assembly without single vote against"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/mar/10/north-koreas-kim-jong-un-elected-assembly-vote-against |date=20140317111316 }} The Guardian 2014 3 10</ref>。他們解釋今次的選舉所有選區也只有一名由朝鮮勞動黨議定的候選人﹔選民既不得不投票，也不得對候選人投反對票<ref name="bbc"/><ref name="economist"/><ref name="guardian"/>。故此，媒體一致認為這場選舉只不過是一場不民主的假選舉<ref name="bbc"/><ref name="economist"/><ref name="guardian"/>。

對於選舉結果，熟悉鄰國政局的南韓傳媒均稱不出意外。其中，[[韓聯社|韓聯社]]稱當選名單沒有出乎意料的變動，說明北韓的政局沒有因金正恩登位而出現劇變<ref name="xinhua">[http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2014-03/12/c_126253093.htm 朝鮮代議員名單被稱“不意外” 金汝靜未出現] 《環球時報》 2014 3 12</ref>。《世界日報》分析，當選者多為50歲左右的勞動黨高級幹部。由此可見，平壤政府注重高層的新老平衡，並已進入世代交替期<ref name="xinhua"/>。[[韓國統一部|韓國統一部]]也認為是次選舉的結果很正常<ref>[http://news.china.com.cn/2014-03/12/content_31755013.htm 崔龙海等当选代议员 韩称朝鲜政局无重大变化迹象] {{Wayback|url=http://news.china.com.cn/2014-03/12/content_31755013.htm |date=20140315143415 }} 《中國網》 2014 3 12</ref>。

